{"index": 145, "title": "Engineering Year In Industry", "job_location": "Bradford-On-Avon, England, United Kingdom", "jd_text": "Job DescriptionAs an AB Dynamics Year in Industry Engineering student, you will gain hands-on experience working on cutting-edge automotive test systems, including track-based solutions (such as driving robots and ADAS targets) and laboratory-based equipment (such as SPMM and ANVH). You will support engineering teams in real-world projects, contributing to design, development, testing, and troubleshooting activities. This placement offers a unique opportunity to apply your academic knowledge in a practical environment, develop technical and professional skills, and gain insight into the automotive testing industry.We are looking for year in industry students in Systems Engineering, Electrical & Electronic and Software HMI.Systems EngineeringDuring a Year-in-Industry placement within AB Dynamics\u2019 Systems Engineering and V&V team, you\u2019ll gain hands-on experience across the full engineering V-model, contributing to real product development for industry-leading vehicle testing solutions. Working in a highly collaborative environment that brings together multiple engineering disciplines, you\u2019ll support activities covering aspects of SysML system architecture development, requirements management, product change management, verification, validation, and automated test creation. This placement offers an opportunity to engage with every stage of the design process while building practical engineering skills.Electrical & Electronic EngineeringAB Dynamics is offering a Year in Industry placement for Electrical and Electronic Engineering undergraduates to join its Mechanical, Electrical and Electronic Design Engineering team, working on robotic and laboratory test systems for automotive R&D applications. The placement student will support the specification, design and integration of electrical and electronic subsystems, including schema