n team (30 minutes)This short call is designed to tell you more about Kaluza and the specific team you\u2019ll be joining, as well as to ensure that the role is the right fit for youFirst stage interview (1 hour minutes)This interview will be with a hiring manager from one of our engineering teams, this interview will cover both mindset and technical questions. We will also incorporate a 15 coding exercise, so have your screen ready to do some coding.Final Interview Loop (3 hours)Three hours sounds like a long time, but we don\u2019t expect all of these to be completed across one day, but we can support that if you so wish, the three sessions cover the following:Behavioural - We use behavioural interviews to understand how you collaborate, solve problems, and build value for customers through real-world examples.System Design - Our system design interview explores how you approach complex, high-scale problems \u2014 from handling real-time data to building reliable, secure, and scalable systems.Pairing - Our pairing interview focuses on problem-solving, clean code, and real-time collaboration \u2014 you'll work through a practical task with one of our engineers.Kaluza ValuesHere at Kaluza we have five core values that guide us as a business:Play to win, Solve the real problem, Build trust every day, Own the outcome, Go further togetherFrom us you\u2019ll getPension SchemeDiscretionary Bonus SchemePrivate Medical Insurance + Virtual GPLife AssuranceAccess to Furthr - a Climate Action appFree Mortgage Advice and Eye TestsPerks at Work - access to thousands of retail discounts5% Flex Fund to spend on the benefits you want most26 days holidayFlexible bank holidays, giving you an additional 8 days which you can choose to take whenever you likeProgressive leave policies with no qualifying service periods, including 26 weeks full pay if you have a new addition to your familyDedicated personal learning and home office budgetsAnd more\u2026We want the best peopleWe\u2019re keen to meet people from all walks of life \u2014 our view is that the more inclusive we are, the better our work will be. We want to build teams which represent a variety of experiences, perspectives and skills, and we recognise talent on the basis of merit and potential.We understand some people may not apply for jobs unless they tick every box. But if you're excited about joining us and think you have some of what we're looking for, even if you're not 100% sure, we'd still love to hear from you.Find out more about working at Kaluza on our careers page and LinkedIn.You can also find our Applicant Data Protection Policy here.\n\nBegin your response with {\n", "v15_labels": {"loc_raw": "London, England, United Kingdom (Hybrid)", "loc": "IN_LONDON", "arr_raw": "Hybrid", "arr": "HYBRID", "sen_raw": "Site Reliability Engineer (release Engineering)", "sen": "LEVEL_2", "tech_raw": "TypeScript, GitHub Actions, AWS, Terraform, Kubernetes, ArgoCD, Datadog, React, Python", "tech": ["REACT", "JS_TS"], "comp_raw": "\u00a340,000 - \u00a360,000", "comp": "RANGE_45_54K"}}
{"index": 169, "title": "Lead Full Stack Engineer (perm) - TypeScript / Next.js / Node.js", "job_location": "Edinburgh, Scotland, United Kingdom", "jd_text": "Job title: Lead Full Stack Engineer (TypeScript / Next.js / Node.js)Type: Full-time, PermanentLocation: UK (flexible home, office, or hybrid working)UK offices: Edinburgh, Newcastle, Leeds, Manchester and LondonStart date: Early MarchPlease note that to be considered for this role, you must be based within 30 miles of one of our UK offices.What You\u2019ll DoYou\u2019ll lead the build of a premium, subscription-based web product used by senior decision makers.You\u2019ll work hands-on across the full stack. TypeScript end-to-end. You\u2019ll build secure, scalable applications with a strong focus on quality and user experience.A lot of the core data already exists. Your job is to help shape how it\u2019s delivered and presented in a way that feels clear, polished and trustworthy.You\u2019ll build and maintain backend services, APIs, and supporting processes. You\u2019ll contribute to a frontend experience that\u2019s fast, clean, and responsive across devices.This is a delivery-focused role. You\u2019ll guide technical decisions, set engineering standards, and support others through good practice and clear direction.You\u2019ll also work closely with an external engineering team. Knowledge transfer and long-term maintainability are key. The goal is software that can be owned, operated, and extended with confidence.What\u2019s In It For YouYou\u2019ll work on a high-profile product where quality genuinely matters. Users will notice the difference between \u201cgood enough\u201d and \u201cexcellent\u201d.You\u2019ll have real ownership from day one. You\u2019ll help shape the approach, not just implement someone else\u2019s plan.You\u2019ll be trusted to lead delivery while staying hands-on. This is not a role where leadership means stepping away from the code.You\u2019ll work in a team that values clear thinkin